INSERT INTO `tbl_about` VALUES (1,'<p><span style=\"color: rgb(34,34,34);font-size: 12pt;font-family: Montserrat;\">Youth Engagement in Agriculture Network (YEAN) is a private youth-led enterprise committed to fostering sustainable agricultural practices. Founded in 2014 with the mission to engage young people to empower farmers and agripreneurs, YEAN core business revolves around the provision of private agriculture extension and advisory services, Access to quality farm inputs and running YEAN commercial demo farms and capacity building through YEAN Private Extension and Advisory Learning Program (PEALE).</span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(34,34,34);font-size: 12pt;font-family: Montserrat;\">YEAN use its youth led models to create and negotiate contracts in agriculture including capacity building, maintaining accurate records and ensuring compliance with all legal and regulatory requirements. YEAN facilitates the sale of essential farm inputs and equipment to over 12,000 farmers through the YEAN Network of over 45,000 farmers, agricultural experts, buyers, and consumers. At the intersection of YEAN’ s work is YEAN proven model “YEAN youth led models”, which are agriculture initiatives where capacitated young people design, implement and lead sustainable agriculture projects and programs that address issues that are important to them and their community. We empower aspired youth to take ownership of their lives and contribute positively to jobs and wealth creation of themselves and their communities while they enable YEAN to scale from a small to a large enterprise</span><span style=\"color: rgb(34,34,34);font-size: 12pt;font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">.</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n','<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(314155/var(--tw-text-opacity));background-color: rgb(255,255,255);font-size: 0.875rem;font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\">YEAN was established in 2014 with the main aim of connecting farmers to useful information in their farming activities. Using technology facilities, YEAN connected the youth to unlock their potential in transforming Agriculture into a sustainable source of income and job creation in Rwanda. Farmers were lacking access to most valuable information in their daily life. YEAN created platforms of farmers, which allow them to have information at the right time. We believe that the transfer of technology and skills from content owners and researchers to farmers is a key solution to the skills gaps we have in accessing what’s needed to be a professional farmer.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(314155/var(--tw-text-opacity));background-color: rgb(255,255,255);font-size: 0.875rem;font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\">Since its creation, YEAN have inspired hundreds of youth to start professional farming activities and have significantly contributed to farming technology upgrade among farmers. YEAN have been creating contents for its agriculture extension services and has acquired extensive experience in what information needed, where it is needed and how to transfer it to be adopted by farmers. YEAN have implemented a number of research and extension projects in collaboration with individual farmers, farmers’ organizations and development organizations in both animal and crop production. This journey has shaped our understanding of extension and advisory sector and have contributed to our goal of creating jobs to young professionals in agriculture to contribute to agriculture transformation</span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n','<p><span style=\"color: rgb(34,34,34);font-size: 12pt;font-family: Montserrat;\">Transforming traditional subsistence agriculture into agribusiness through youth innovations as skilled and powerful weapon for leading the change toward sustainable livelihood.</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n','<p><span style=\"color: rgb(34,34,34);font-size: 12pt;font-family: Montserrat;\">Spread agriculture information and facts to the community to inspire change for the pursuit of beauty and excellence in young agripreneurs and the community.</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n','/uploads/media-1703764896852-676872229.jpeg');
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `tbl_about` ENABLE KEYS */;
UNLOCK TABLES;

