INSERT INTO `tbl_team` VALUES (1,'<p><span style=\"color: black;font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">NSHIMIYIMANA Arcade is the Executive Secretary of YEAN. He is agronomist by profession, a farmer and agribusiness expert. Prior to this role, Arcade has been working with various NGOs and private companies in agriculture development projects and programs and he received several professional trainings in Private agriculture extension, Agriculture Water Management, Livestock Production, Agribusiness to name a few. Arcade holds a bachelor’s degree in agriculture and rural development from former ISAE Busogo, with over 10 years’ work experience in community-based programs especially rural economic development projects, agribusiness and youth capacity building programs. Arcade served as a Board member of Rwanda Youth Agribusiness Forum (RYAF) in the period of 2018-2020.</span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n','Arcade Nshimiyimana','Executive Secretary','/uploads/media-1703695010890-480498492.jpeg'),(3,'<p>Merveille is a young and dynamic professional passionate about governance, development, and finance. The professional exposure and experience have grown her capacities and desire to contribute to the advancement of the finance field and prosperous society especially through influencing fellow youth to be confident and rise in the field of finance. Merveille holds a bachelor’s degree in business accounting and economics specialized in Finance. Currently pursuing a master’s degree in project management and CPA candidate.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n','Merveille Uwineza','Finance Manager','/uploads/media-1703697095226-199856374.jpeg'),(4,'<p>Cecile is an agronomist with a bachelor’s degree in crop production from the former National University of Rwanda and post graduate diploma in Agriculture from Israel. With more than 7 years of experience in agronomy related work, Cecile has strong knowledge of agriculture extension, irrigation technology, horticulture and cereal production, mushrooms production, green house and hydroponic technologies.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n','Cecile Niyireba','Agriculture Extension Officer ','/uploads/media-1703699458161-466590291.jpeg'),(6,'<p>INGABIRE Rosine is a dedicated accountant who previously worked with commercial banks dealing with bank’s customer transactions and handling the customer complains. Rosine has over 3 years of experience in accounting with a good working command of accounting software including Quickbooks, Sage and taxes declaration.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n','Rosine Ingabire','Accountant','/uploads/media-1703757032529-426516744.jpeg'),(7,'<p><span style=\"color: rgb(34,34,34);background-color: white;font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">NGABITSINZE </span>Dieudonne is an agronomist with a bachelor’s degree in Crop Production from University of Rwanda, College of Agriculture, Animal Science and Veterinary Medicines (UR-CAVM) and with A2 certificate in Agriculture. Dieudonne has over 5 years of experience on field activity in different projects and organizations with various positions related to agronomy, Agriculture extension and capacity building in different districts of Rwanda.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n','Dieudonne Ngabitsinze','Agriculture Extension Officer ','/uploads/media-1703757457952-974663059.jpeg'),(8,'<p><span style=\"color: rgb(34,34,34);background-color: white;font-size: 12pt;font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Jean is an enthusiastic young person with a great commitment to serving the community. Having served in different companies as a logistic person for more than 3 years, he brought to YEAN a set of skills and commitment to handle logistical issues to enhance quick and effective delivery of services to farmers. He is pursuing his degree in Accounting at theUniversity of Lay Adventist Of Kigali.</span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n','Jean Hakizimana','Logistic Officer','/uploads/media-1703757887932-928677138.jpeg'),(9,'<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-family: Montserrat;\">Stanislas holds a bachelor’s degree in crop science from the National University of Rwanda with a training certificate in Climate-smart agriculture, Nutrition-sensitive agriculture, sustainable agriculture productivity, and gender mainstreaming.</span> <span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-family: Montserrat;\">Before joining YEAN, Stanislas worked as</span> <span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-family: Montserrat;\">City Coordinator in the NICE Project funded by SDC and coordinated by Sight and Life Rwanda,</span> <span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-family: Montserrat;\">District Supervisor in the community-based climate change adaptation project implemented by NBDF-Rwanda funded by EU, Agriculture Loan officer in Urwego Bank, Farmer Enterprise Development Officer in Zamuka Cooperative funded by Vi</span> <span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-family: Montserrat;\">Agro-forestry, and District agriculture productivity</span> <span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-family: Montserrat;\">Officer for</span> <span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-family: Montserrat;\">Hinga Weze Project funded by USAID implemented by Imbaraga Farmer organization a subcontractor of CNFA. Stanislas’s hobbies out of work includes praying, singing, and doing sports.</span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n','Stanislas Musange','District Project Coordinator ','/uploads/media-1705160039227-391728042.jpeg'),(10,'<p><span style=\"font-family: Montserrat;\">Jean Richard MIGAMBI holds a Bachelor of Science with honors in crop production from the University of Rwanda College of Agriculture Animal Science and Veterinary Medicine (UR-CAVM) since 2014 with a Diploma on agriculture training (learn by doing) from Israel. Before joining YEAN he served in different organizations including Field Collaborator for WAMCAB project; RYAF Horticulturist with SAIP project; Cooperative agronomist funded by RSSP; Atlantis microfinance Ltd in E-Muhinzi project; Direct marketing of different varieties of bio fortified beans seeds for Harvest Plus in collaboration with RAB. Richard hobbies out of work are singing jogging and gardening. </span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n','Jean Richard MIGAMBI  ','District Project Coordinator ','/uploads/media-1705160154681-499572045.jpeg'),(11,'<p>Patrick Ngabonziza holds a bachelor\'s degree in agribusiness from UNIK with a professional certificate in feeding A hungry planet, Hydroponics farming technology, Organic agriculture, Agricultural extension video production, to name a few.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Before joining YEAN as District project coordinator, Patrick worked as trainer and farmer\'s coach in different organisation, including One Acre fund, RYAF, FIATA, Veto mobile.  Patrick hobbies are charity\'s activities, business show and classical music.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n','Patrick Ngabonziza','District Project Coordinator ','/uploads/media-1711471968428-836476005.jpeg');
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `tbl_team` ENABLE KEYS */;
UNLOCK TABLES;

