INSERT INTO `user` VALUES (483,'member','jeanwilsontwizerimana@gmail.com','6a076c14aca8d7d32016ce0fd29425ec','Kaminuza A0|A0','2017-12-17 19:18:52','Jean Wilson','TWIZERIMANA','0789518971','male','1993-05-18 00:00:00','Northern Province','Gakenke','','small scale poultry farming','GAKENKE','My agriculture practice is based on  poultry farming','',0,0,NULL,NULL),(469,'member','niyiroraenockjeanbosco@gmail.com','58c417394740c6a9469de879efc8a8a4','Kaminuza A0|A0','2017-11-11 17:51:35','NIYIRORA','ENOCK JEAN BOSCO','+250785695297','male','1988-01-04 00:00:00','Kigali City','Nyarugege','','Mixed farming: Horticulture','Mixed farming: Horticulture','Imboga, Ibihumyo n\'ibihingwa ngandurarugo','',0,0,NULL,NULL),(474,'member','umugisolange@gmail.com','f8c7e4a1face7334dfa5445dad470e8d','Kaminuza A0|A0','2017-11-25 16:11:31','Solange','Mugiraneza','0785092267/0725240395','female','1993-02-06 00:00:00','Southern Province','Gisagara','Kansi','Arachides','Gisagara/kansi','Agriculture based on groundnuts and I prefer their transformatik','',0,0,NULL,NULL),(475,'member','nchristella18@gmail.com','bba63a39d20d3be2ef3d2df867d85091','Kaminuza A0|A0','2017-11-29 12:58:00','Christella ','Mukakalisa','+250788699514','female','1988-01-01 00:00:00','Kigali City','Gasabo','Kanjongo','Corns and Tomatoes','KOPERATIVE CODIKA','Agriculture and horticulture is among the top priorities of the Government of Rwanda. The horticulture industry in Rwanda is committed to the production of high quality and environmentally friendly products while ensuring the health and welfare of the consumers. It offers considerable potential and can contribute positively to poverty reduction and economic development if adequately exploited. \r\nI am involved in KOPERATIVE CODICA for growing corns and tomatoes which are highly demanded on both the local & international markets. Nevertheless, the sector is still facing some challenges. Among others, the lack of policies that provide what is needed to improve production, including innovation, and with the necessary investment. Currently, I participate actively in organization of regional horticulture networking activities to discuss challenges and co-create solutions to promote the regional trade in Horticulture Sector. I believe that with the skills that I have and what I gain in the network contribute to the revision of better & stable agricultural, food & trade policies to ensure that the horticultural farms productivity is increased and enhance food security (the availability, accessibility and affordability of food).\r\n\r\n','',0,0,NULL,NULL),(481,'member','manipthegrede@gmail.com','8328f750b49401ac999987747592ecfd','Kaminuza A0|A0','2017-12-14 18:34:13','Joseph','MANIRAKIZA','0786515313/0725927611','male','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Kigali City','Gasabo','Gishubi',' urutoki(banana)','Gishubi','just agriculture is major source of income of people in developing country that is why is important to focus more and more on it , may be through in subsidies (agriculture extension) to the farmers ,free training as usually done lead to improve agriculture technology also cause farmers change mind in this form  from growing owner consumption to growing plant which produce high production in order to remain these production on going in the market we remember that last agriculture is experienced by local breeds,more inter cropping system but not to day  is there are  hy breed and mono culture which leading high production even problem is there probably is accept rather than before  may be price decrease ,food waste for perishable good gives farmer loss','',0,0,NULL,NULL),(310,'member','vestidu07@gmail.com','ab2c9963742b7e52f8f09222548f43c8','Kaminuza A0|A0','2017-04-04 06:54:19','DUKESHIMANA','Vestine','0725953016/0788325767','female','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Northern Province','Gakenke','','imiteja,amashu n\'ibishyimbo','akarere ka Rulindo,umurenge wa base,umudugudu wa gitovu','Ubuhinzi bwange nkuko nabivuze higanjemo horticultural crops arik